  <heading>Bicycles</heading>
  <section>
    <prefix>Regulation</prefix>
    <num>.01</num>
    <heading>Smooth Surface.</heading>
    <text>A bike lane or shoulder shall be considered to have a smooth surface if that surface has a texture equal to or better than the adjacent roadway, and if the surface contains undulations which are no larger than the adjacent roadway.</text>
